description:
&lt;p&gt;We, the Pulmonary Hypertension (PH) team, based within the Heart and Lung unit at Great Ormond Street Hospital are looking for an experienced paediatric nurse to join our team as a 2nd Nurse Specialist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are the only centre in the UK providing specialist care for Children with Pulmonary Hypertension and we are the largest paediatric pulmonary hypertension service in Europe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using a shared care model, we take our expertise and knowledge out to the PH patients in 8 paediatric cardiac centres around the UK on a regular basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applicants with cardiology experience, although Paediatric ITU/ Respiratory/Community/Palliative care / GUCH nursing are also very relevant to this post. Our patient group is looking for a dynamic enthusiastic nurse with exceptional communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is ideal for someone who would like to bring their skills into our specialist paediatric service. In return you will join a friendly and dynamic multi professional team. We are committed to staff development and are able to provide comprehensive career development. The specialist nature of the work offers nurses the opportunity to develop levels of expertise second to none.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rebecca Turquet CNS for Pulmonary Hypertension on 02074059200 ext. 1007 or by email rebecca.turquet@gosh.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also welcome informal visits.&lt;/p&gt;
